#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
semantic-checker — Script 6 of the ClarityRev 25-niche evaluation pipeline.

Google SRE pattern: software engineering for operations.

Purpose: Replace the deterministic grade engine (binary criteria only) with
a semantic verifier that uses the Claude API to evaluate whether a source
actually supports a claim. A fabricated claim with a real URL passes all 4
binary checks — this script catches that gap.

Cost control: Only 20% of claims are semantically verified per run (deterministic
hash-based sampling), plus ALL claims in CRITICAL sections (market_size,
competitive_threat, revenue_leak). Non-sampled claims receive a deterministic-only
marker.

Input:  research/{niche_id}/evidence-claims.json
        JSON array of { claim_text, source_url, section, trace_map_id }

Output: research/{niche_id}/evidence-grades-semantic.json
        JSON object with per-claim grades, sampling metadata, and alerts

Usage:
    # Full run for one niche
    python3 semantic-checker --niche N-001

    # Dry run (no API calls — report what would be checked)
    python3 semantic-checker --niche N-001 --dry-run

    # Agent mode (compact JSON output, no stderr)
    python3 semantic-checker --niche N-001 --agent-mode

    # Custom model
    python3 semantic-checker --niche N-001 --model claude-opus-4-20250514
"""

